Qt Jambi - Qt-Java binding
http://qtjambi.org

-----

Same as Java-Gnome library, QT Jambi is a QT Binding to Java, allowing you to develop QT GUI using Java instead of C++.

Install Qt Jambi from its PPA:
sudo apt-add-repository 'deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/qtjambi-community/libqtjambi/ubuntu maverick main' 
sudo apt-get update 
sudo apt-get install libqtjambi


Open Eclipse, Create a Java Project and add external libraries from /usr/share/java/
Adding the qtjambi.jar does the job.

-----

Source code at https://qt.gitorious.org/qt-jambi

-----

Install Qt Designer:

sudo apt-get install qt4-designer

-----

Old designer integration (deprecated now!)

Qt Jambi integrates with QT Designer

Go to your Terminal and type:

qtjambi-designer.sh

or

bash /usr/bin/qtjambi-designer.sh
